# Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)
The following artifacts were identified during timeline review as potentially indicative of malicious activity.
## 1. Multiple failed authentication attempts
A short burst of failed login attempts occurred before a successful login.  
This pattern may indicate credential guessing or brute-force activity.
## 2. Successful login from an unfamiliar source
The successful authentication following multiple failures suggests possible unauthorized access especially if the source differs from normal usage patterns.
## 3. Unrecognized process execution
A background process was observed that had not been previously documented in the system baseline activity.  
Unexpected process creation after authentication can indicate payload execution.
## 4. Outbound Network Connection to External Address
An outbound connection occurred shortly after the new process was launched.  
Unexpected external communication may indicate command-and-control (C2) activity or data exfiltration attempts.

These indicators individually may not confirm compromise but their sequence and correlation increase the likelihood of malicious activity.
